      <akn:section eId="sec_2_360_05">
        <akn:num>2-360.05</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Appeal of Board decisions.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-360_05_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A contractor may appeal a Board decision to the District of Columbia Court of Appeals within 120 days after the date of receipt of a copy of the decision.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-360_05_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If the CPO determines that an appeal should be taken, the CPO, with the prior approval of the Office of the Attorney General, may appeal the Board’s decision to the District of Columbia Court of Appeals for judicial review within 120 days from the date of the receipt of the Board’s decision.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
